<p>Now, we=E2=80=99ll introduce the <a href=3D"https://go.dev/src/crypto/ci=
pher/gcm.go">GCM</a> (Galois/Counter Mode), a powerful encryption method. G=
CM is a cryptographic mode of operation that combines the security of a sym=
metric block cipher (like AES) with message authentication.</p>
<p>GCM does two key things. First, it encrypts data, making it unreadable t=
o unauthorized eyes. Second, it generates a tag (checksum) that verifies th=
e data's integrity during decryption. Any modification to the ciphertext wi=
ll result in a verification failure.</p>
